# Factory Session Start — Mandatory Checks

Before doing ANY work in this repo, perform these checks in order.
Do NOT skip any of them. Do NOT assume state is correct.

## 1. Read OPERATIONS.md

Read `OPERATIONS.md` for the canonical start/stop/verify procedures.

## 2. Verify .env

Read `.env` and confirm ALL of these are correct:

- `FACTORY_AGENT_PROVIDER_ORDER=codex,openai_api,deterministic`
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` is non-empty and starts with `sk-`
- `EXECUTION_REPO_ROOT=` (empty, no path)
- `EXECUTION_PORTFOLIO_STATE_ROOT=data/portfolios`

If anything is wrong, fix it BEFORE proceeding. This is the #1 cause
of factory breakage.

## 3. Check git state

- `git status` on main — look for uncommitted work
- Check if `bng` worktree has unpushed commits:
  `git -C ~/.cursor/worktrees/AgenticTrading/bng log --oneline main..HEAD`
- If there are unmerged commits, merge them to main first

## 4. Verify services

- Dashboard: `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8787/ | head -c 100`
- Factory loop: `ps aux | grep factory_loop | grep -v grep`
- If either is down, start it (see OPERATIONS.md)

## 5. Never do these things

- Never set `EXECUTION_REPO_ROOT` to any path
- Never remove `openai_api` from the provider chain
- Never start the dashboard on port 8788
- Never skip the `.env` verification step
